{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":547,"text":"I thought I'd talk a little bit\nabout how nature makes materials."},{"time":3738,"text":"I brought along with me an abalone shell."},{"time":5952,"text":"This abalone shell\nis a biocomposite material"},{"time":8551,"text":"that's 98 percent by mass\ncalcium carbonate"},{"time":11424,"text":"and two percent by mass protein."},{"time":13979,"text":"Yet, it's 3,000 times tougher\nthan its geological counterpart."},{"time":17699,"text":"And a lot of people might use\nstructures like abalone shells,"},{"time":21162,"text":"like chalk."},{"time":22338,"text":"I've been fascinated\nby how nature makes materials,"},{"time":25153,"text":"and there's a lot of secrets\nto how they do such an exquisite job."},{"time":28532,"text":"Part of it is that these materials\nare macroscopic in structure,"},{"time":32824,"text":"but they're formed at the nano scale."},{"time":34707,"text":"They're formed at the nano scale,"},{"time":36399,"text":"and they use proteins\nthat are coded by the genetic level"},{"time":40056,"text":"that allow them to build\nthese really exquisite structures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":42889,"text":"So something I think\nis very fascinating is:"},{"time":45145,"text":"What if you could give life\nto non-living structures,"},{"time":49426,"text":"like batteries and like solar cells?"},{"time":51700,"text":"What if they had\nsome of the same capabilities"},{"time":54008,"text":"that an abalone shell did,"},{"time":55700,"text":"in terms of being able\nto build really exquisite structures"},{"time":59406,"text":"at room temperature and room pressure,"},{"time":61263,"text":"using nontoxic chemicals"},{"time":63332,"text":"and adding no toxic materials\nback into the environment?"},{"time":66055,"text":"So that's kind of the vision\nthat I've been thinking about."},{"time":69337,"text":"And so what if you could grow\na battery in a Petri dish?"},{"time":72027,"text":"Or what if you could give\ngenetic information to a battery"},{"time":74941,"text":"so that it could actually become\nbetter as a function of time, and do so"},{"time":78767,"text":"in an environmentally friendly way?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":80935,"text":"And so, going back to this abalone shell,"},{"time":84030,"text":"besides being nanostructured,\none thing that's fascinating is,"},{"time":87119,"text":"when a male and female\nabalone get together,"},{"time":89611,"text":"they pass on the genetic\ninformation that says,"},{"time":91840,"text":"\"This is how to build\nan exquisite material."},{"time":94300,"text":"Here's how to do it at room\ntemperature and pressure,"},{"time":96824,"text":"using nontoxic materials.\""},{"time":98154,"text":"Same with diatoms,\nwhich are shown right here,"},{"time":100342,"text":"which are glasseous structures."},{"time":101989,"text":"Every time the diatoms replicate,"},{"time":103700,"text":"they give the genetic\ninformation that says,"},{"time":105790,"text":"\"Here's how to build glass in the ocean\nthat's perfectly nanostructured.\""},{"time":109478,"text":"And you can do it the same,\nover and over again.\""},{"time":111795,"text":"So what if you could do the same thing\nwith a solar cell or a battery?"},{"time":115139,"text":"I like to say my favorite\nbiomaterial is my four year old."}]},{"cues":[{"time":118700,"text":"But anyone who's ever had\nor knows small children knows,"},{"time":121961,"text":"they're incredibly complex organisms."},{"time":124001,"text":"If you wanted to convince them to do\nsomething they don't want to do,"},{"time":127721,"text":"it's very difficult."},{"time":128903,"text":"So when we think\nabout future technologies,"},{"time":130943,"text":"we actually think of using\nbacteria and viruses --"},{"time":134185,"text":"simple organisms."},{"time":135417,"text":"Can you convince them\nto work with a new toolbox,"},{"time":138097,"text":"so they can build a structure\nthat will be important to me?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":141371,"text":"Also, when we think\nabout future technologies,"},{"time":143696,"text":"we start with the beginning of Earth."},{"time":145933,"text":"Basically, it took a billion years\nto have life on Earth."},{"time":149700,"text":"And very rapidly,\nthey became multi-cellular,"},{"time":151835,"text":"they could replicate,\nthey could use photosynthesis"},{"time":154436,"text":"as a way of getting their energy source."},{"time":156397,"text":"But it wasn't until about 500\nmillion years ago --"},{"time":158763,"text":"during the Cambrian\ngeologic time period --"},{"time":160819,"text":"that organisms in the ocean\nstarted making hard materials."},{"time":163888,"text":"Before that, they were all\nsoft, fluffy structures."},{"time":167476,"text":"It was during this time\nthat there was increased calcium,"},{"time":170188,"text":"iron and silicon in the environment,"},{"time":172068,"text":"and organisms learned\nhow to make hard materials."},{"time":175334,"text":"So that's what I would like\nto be able to do,"},{"time":177549,"text":"convince biology to work\nwith the rest of the periodic table."}]},{"cues":[{"time":181200,"text":"Now, if you look at biology,"},{"time":183412,"text":"there's many structures like DNA,\nantibodies, proteins and ribosomes"},{"time":187254,"text":"you've heard about,"},{"time":188478,"text":"that are nanostructured --"},{"time":189948,"text":"nature already gives us really exquisite\nstructures on the nano scale."},{"time":193480,"text":"What if we could harness them"},{"time":195203,"text":"and convince them to not be an antibody\nthat does something like HIV?"},{"time":199925,"text":"What if we could convince them\nto build a solar cell for us?"},{"time":204074,"text":"Here are some examples."},{"time":205448,"text":"Natural shells,\nnatural biological materials."},{"time":207629,"text":"The abalone shell here."},{"time":208845,"text":"If you fracture it, you can look\nat the fact that it's nanostructured."},{"time":212256,"text":"There's diatoms made out of SiO2,"},{"time":214408,"text":"and there are magnetotactic bacteria"},{"time":216290,"text":"that make small, single-domain\nmagnets used for navigation."},{"time":219700,"text":"What all these have in common"},{"time":221392,"text":"is these materials\nare structured at the nano scale,"},{"time":223973,"text":"and they have a DNA sequence\nthat codes for a protein sequence"},{"time":227323,"text":"that gives them the blueprint"},{"time":228853,"text":"to be able to build\nthese really wonderful structures."},{"time":231700,"text":"Now, going back to the abalone shell,"},{"time":233906,"text":"the abalone makes this shell\nby having these proteins."},{"time":236510,"text":"These proteins\nare very negatively charged."},{"time":238558,"text":"They can pull calcium\nout of the environment,"},{"time":240757,"text":"and put down a layer of calcium\nand then carbonate, calcium and carbonate."},{"time":244320,"text":"It has the chemical sequences\nof amino acids which says,"},{"time":247237,"text":"\"This is how to build the structure."},{"time":248984,"text":"Here's the DNA sequence,\nhere's the protein sequence"},{"time":251452,"text":"in order to do it.\""},{"time":252627,"text":"So an interesting idea is,"},{"time":253898,"text":"what if you could take\nany material you wanted,"},{"time":256175,"text":"or any element on the periodic table,"},{"time":257977,"text":"and find its corresponding DNA sequence,"},{"time":260359,"text":"then code it for a corresponding\nprotein sequence to build a structure,"},{"time":264070,"text":"but not build an abalone shell --"},{"time":265730,"text":"build something that nature has never had\nthe opportunity to work with yet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":270954,"text":"And so here's the periodic table."},{"time":273296,"text":"I absolutely love the periodic table."},{"time":275107,"text":"Every year for the incoming\nfreshman class at MIT,"},{"time":277756,"text":"I have a periodic table made that says,"},{"time":279707,"text":"\"Welcome to MIT.\nNow you're in your element.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":281868,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":282901,"text":"And you flip it over,\nand it's the amino acids"},{"time":285214,"text":"with the pH at which they have\ndifferent charges."},{"time":287700,"text":"And so I give this out\nto thousands of people."},{"time":290700,"text":"And I know it says MIT\nand this is Caltech,"},{"time":292820,"text":"but I have a couple extra\nif people want it."},{"time":294908,"text":"I was really fortunate to have\nPresident Obama visit my lab this year"},{"time":299251,"text":"on his visit to MIT,"},{"time":300664,"text":"and I really wanted to give\nhim a periodic table."},{"time":302986,"text":"So I stayed up at night\nand talked to my husband,"},{"time":305352,"text":"\"How do I give President Obama\na periodic table?"},{"time":307632,"text":"What if he says,\n'Oh, I already have one,'"},{"time":309724,"text":"or, 'I've already memorized it?'\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":311388,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":312420,"text":"So he came to visit my lab and looked\naround -- it was a great visit."},{"time":315724,"text":"And then afterward, I said,"},{"time":317082,"text":"\"Sir, I want to give you\nthe periodic table,"},{"time":319469,"text":"in case you're ever in a bind\nand need to calculate molecular weight.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":322856,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":323966,"text":"I thought \"molecular weight\" sounded\nmuch less nerdy than \"molar mass.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":327504,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":328599,"text":"And he looked at it and said,"},{"time":331522,"text":"\"Thank you. I'll look at it periodically.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":333560,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":335700,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":339700,"text":"Later in a lecture\nthat he gave on clean energy,"},{"time":342700,"text":"he pulled it out and said,"},{"time":344024,"text":"\"And people at MIT,\nthey give out periodic tables.\" So ..."}]},{"cues":[{"time":346786,"text":"So basically what I didn't tell you"},{"time":349118,"text":"is that about 500 million years ago,\nthe organisms started making materials,"},{"time":352743,"text":"but it took them about 50 million years\nto get good at it --"},{"time":355601,"text":"50 million years to learn how to perfect\nhow to make that abalone shell."},{"time":359072,"text":"And that's a hard sell\nto a graduate student:"},{"time":361220,"text":"\"I have this great project ...\n50 million years ...\""},{"time":363781,"text":"So we had to develop a way\nof trying to do this more rapidly."},{"time":367309,"text":"And so we use a nontoxic virus\ncalled M13 bacteriophage,"},{"time":372086,"text":"whose job is to infect bacteria."},{"time":374067,"text":"Well, it has a simple DNA structure"},{"time":375797,"text":"that you can go in and cut and paste\nadditional DNA sequences into it,"},{"time":379949,"text":"and by doing that, it allows the virus\nto express random protein sequences."}]},{"cues":[{"time":384466,"text":"This is pretty easy biotechnology,"},{"time":386403,"text":"and you could basically\ndo this a billion times."},{"time":388674,"text":"So you can have\na billion different viruses"},{"time":391008,"text":"that are all genetically identical,"},{"time":392739,"text":"but they differ from each other\nbased on their tips,"},{"time":395201,"text":"on one sequence,"},{"time":396826,"text":"that codes for one protein."},{"time":398339,"text":"Now if you take all billion viruses,\nand put them in one drop of liquid,"},{"time":402117,"text":"you can force them to interact\nwith anything you want"},{"time":404650,"text":"on the periodic table."},{"time":405855,"text":"And through a process\nof selection evolution,"},{"time":407996,"text":"you can pull one of a billion\nthat does something you'd like it to do,"},{"time":411324,"text":"like grow a battery or a solar cell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":413102,"text":"Basically, viruses can't replicate\nthemselves; they need a host."},{"time":416162,"text":"Once you find that one out of a billion,"},{"time":418150,"text":"you infect it into a bacteria,\nand make millions and billions of copies"},{"time":421611,"text":"of that particular sequence."},{"time":423023,"text":"The other thing\nthat's beautiful about biology"},{"time":425225,"text":"is that biology gives you\nreally exquisite structures"},{"time":428391,"text":"with nice link scales."},{"time":429700,"text":"These viruses are long and skinny,"},{"time":431535,"text":"and we can get them to express the ability"},{"time":433724,"text":"to grow something like semiconductors"},{"time":435700,"text":"or materials for batteries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":437830,"text":"Now, this is a high-powered\nbattery that we grew in my lab."},{"time":440700,"text":"We engineered a virus\nto pick up carbon nanotubes."},{"time":443437,"text":"One part of the virus\ngrabs a carbon nanotube,"},{"time":445700,"text":"the other part of the virus has a sequence"},{"time":447809,"text":"that can grow an electrode\nmaterial for a battery,"},{"time":450457,"text":"and then it wires itself\nto the current collector."},{"time":453180,"text":"And so through a process\nof selection evolution,"},{"time":455700,"text":"we went from being able to have\na virus that made a crummy battery"},{"time":458866,"text":"to a virus that made a good battery"},{"time":460571,"text":"to a virus that made a record-breaking,\nhigh-powered battery"},{"time":463467,"text":"that's all made at room temperature,\nbasically at the benchtop."},{"time":466658,"text":"That battery went to the White House\nfor a press conference,"},{"time":470152,"text":"and I brought it here."},{"time":471587,"text":"You can see it in this case\nthat's lighting this LED."},{"time":474390,"text":"Now if we could scale this,"},{"time":476469,"text":"you could actually use it\nto run your Prius,"},{"time":480453,"text":"which is kind of my dream --\nto be able to drive a virus-powered car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483821,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":484962,"text":"But basically you can pull\none out of a billion,"},{"time":489700,"text":"and make lots of amplifications to it."},{"time":491642,"text":"Basically, you make\nan amplification in the lab,"},{"time":493939,"text":"and then you get it to self-assemble\ninto a structure like a battery."},{"time":497257,"text":"We're able to do this also with catalysis."},{"time":499547,"text":"This is the example\nof a photocatalytic splitting of water."},{"time":503502,"text":"And what we've been able to do\nis engineer a virus"},{"time":506514,"text":"to basically take dye-absorbing molecules"},{"time":508824,"text":"and line them up\non the surface of the virus"},{"time":510903,"text":"so it acts as an antenna,"},{"time":512238,"text":"and you get an energy transfer\nacross the virus."},{"time":514935,"text":"And then we give it a second gene\nto grow an inorganic material"},{"time":518222,"text":"that can be used to split water\ninto oxygen and hydrogen,"},{"time":522238,"text":"that can be used for clean fuels."},{"time":524476,"text":"I brought an example\nof that with me today."},{"time":526576,"text":"My students promised me it would work."},{"time":528418,"text":"These are virus-assembled nanowires."},{"time":530869,"text":"When you shine light on them,\nyou can see them bubbling."},{"time":533700,"text":"In this case, you're seeing\noxygen bubbles come out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536659,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":537992,"text":"Basically, by controlling the genes,"},{"time":540700,"text":"you can control multiple materials\nto improve your device performance."}]},{"cues":[{"time":544058,"text":"The last example are solar cells."},{"time":545788,"text":"You can also do this with solar cells."},{"time":547627,"text":"We've been able to engineer viruses\nto pick up carbon nanotubes"},{"time":550913,"text":"and then grow titanium\ndioxide around them,"},{"time":555040,"text":"and use it as a way of getting\nelectrons through the device."},{"time":559083,"text":"And what we've found\nis through genetic engineering,"},{"time":561571,"text":"we can actually increase\nthe efficiencies of these solar cells"},{"time":566398,"text":"to record numbers"},{"time":568399,"text":"for these types of dye-sensitized systems."},{"time":571700,"text":"And I brought one of those as well,"},{"time":573700,"text":"that you can play around\nwith outside afterward."},{"time":576902,"text":"So this is a virus-based solar cell."},{"time":578791,"text":"Through evolution and selection,"},{"time":580700,"text":"we took it from an eight percent\nefficiency solar cell"},{"time":584220,"text":"to an 11 percent efficiency solar cell."}]},{"cues":[{"time":586328,"text":"So I hope that I've convinced you"},{"time":588185,"text":"that there's a lot of great,\ninteresting things to be learned"},{"time":592076,"text":"about how nature makes materials,"},{"time":593700,"text":"and about taking it the next step,"},{"time":595375,"text":"to see if you can force or take advantage\nof how nature makes materials,"},{"time":599896,"text":"to make things that nature\nhasn't yet dreamed of making."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602601,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":603776,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}